title: Why does TypeScript let you assign a RobotDog to a variable typed as Dog? Go!
comment_text: Coz TypeScript determines type compatibility based on the shape or structure of an object, rather than relying on explicit declarations or nominal relationships (like class inheritance in some other languages).
